#- Farewell we call§0
§0to hearth and hall!§0
§0
§0Though wind may blow and rain may fall,§0
§0
§0We must away§0
§0ere break of day§0
§0
§0Far over wood§0
§0and mountain tall.
#- To Rivendell,§0
§0where Elves yet dwell§0
§0
§0In glades beneath§0
§0the misty fell,§0
§0
§0Through moor§0
§0and waste§0
§0we ride in haste,§0
§0
§0And whither then§0
§0we cannot tell.
#- With foes ahead, behind us dread,§0
§0
§0Beneath the sky§0
§0shall be our bed,§0
§0
§0Until at last§0
§0our toil be passed,§0
§0
§0Our journey done,§0
§0our errand sped.
#- We must away!§0
§0
§0We must away!§0
§0
§0We ride before§0
§0the break of day!
